item.title: Julie Andrews turns 80
item.ExtractedText: Julie Andrews turns 80 Updated 1425 GMT (2225 HKT) October 1, 2015 7 photos: Julie Andrews turns 80 British actress and singer Julie Andrews , best known for her roles in "Mary Poppins" and " The Sound of Music ," turns 80 on October 1. Take a look back at some highlights from her career. Hide Caption 7 photos: Julie Andrews turns 80 Actress Julie Andrews and others appear in the play "My Fair Lady" in 1956. Hide Caption 7 photos: Julie Andrews turns 80 Andrews poses with her "Mary Poppins" co-star Dick Van Dyke in 1964. Hide Caption 3 of 7 7 photos: Julie Andrews turns 80 Andrews arrives at the Oscars with her husband, Tony Walton, in 1965. She would leave the ceremony with the Best Actress award for her role in "Mary Poppins." Hide Caption 7 photos: Julie Andrews turns 80 Andrews plays the iconic Maria von Trapp in 1965's "The Sound of Music." Hide Caption 5 of 7 7 photos: Julie Andrews turns 80 In 2001, Andrews was one of five Kennedy Center honorees along with pianist Van Cliburn, actor Jack Nicholson, opera singer Luciano Pavarotti and music maestro Quincy Jones. Hide Caption 6 of 7 7 photos: Julie Andrews turns 80 Lady Gaga introduces Andrews after singing a tribute to "The Sound of Music" at the 2015 Academy Awards. Hide Caption
